#Apache installation

Step 1 — Install Apache
bashsudo apt update
sudo apt install apache2

Step 2 — Start Apache
bashsudo systemctl start apache2
Enable it to start automatically on boot:
bashsudo systemctl enable apache2

Step 3 — Verify Apache is Running
bashsudo systemctl status apache2
You should see:
Active: active (running)

Step 4 — Test in Browser
Open your browser and type:
http://localhost
You should see Apache2 Ubuntu Default Page — a page that says "It works!"

If you see that page — Apache is successfully installed.

Useful Apache Commands to Remember
bashsudo systemctl start apache2      # Start
sudo systemctl stop apache2       # Stop
sudo systemctl restart apache2    # Restart
sudo systemctl status apache2     # Check status